cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with visual object analysis and learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel transfer approach for attribute-based knowledge transfer, which involves learning and transferring attributes between categories. This is a machine learning task, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with semantic attributes, which are a form of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on public datasets, which involves image processing and computer vision (cs.MM).
